summary: One of my personal objectives is to be a professional technologist. I have gotten a degree at Polytechnic School in Delft. I went to the University of Amsterdam to become a professor of Chemistry, Mineralogy, and  Geology. I've also obtained a doctors degree in Holland. I was the first Dutch chemist to have earned a Nobel Prize for my discoveries of chemical equilibrium, osmotic pressure, and stereochemistry. I know how to deal with technical problems.
